        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspection and Verification - Interior Lighting</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the customer concern.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect the following for obvious signs of mechanical or electrical damage.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <table id="t1704004">
                <title>Visual Inspection Chart</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="0.97*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.95*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Mechanical</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Electrical</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Parking brake switch</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Multifunction switch</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Circuitry open/shorted</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Daytime running lamps (DRL) module</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the autolamps and manual control of the headlamps operate correctly before
                    proceeding to the next step.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the parking brake warning indicator operates correctly (the parking brake
                    warning indicator should be illuminated only when the parking brake is engaged). If the parking
                    brake warning indicator does not operate correctly, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s08307_X4130132.xml" xrefid="x4130132">Instrument Cluster</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the concern is not visually evident, verify the symptom. GO to Symptom Chart.</para>
            </step1>
            <table id="t1704005" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>Symptom Chart</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.94*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.90*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.15*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Condition</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Possible Sources</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Action</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The daytime running lamps (DRL) are inoperative</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Circuitry open/ shorted.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Parking brake switch</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Multifunction switch.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Daytime running lamps (DRL) module.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>GO to Pinpoint Test A.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The daytime running lamps are ON with the parking brake set</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Circuitry open.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Parking brake switch.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Daytime running lamps (DRL) module.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Pinpoint Test B.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The daytime running lamps are on with the ignition switch OFF</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Circuitry shorted.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Ignition relay.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Daytime running lamps (DRL) module.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Pinpoint Test C.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pinpoint Tests - Daytime Running Lamps</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="italic">Pinpoint Test A: The Daytime Running Lamps (DRL) Are Inoperative</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Normal Operation</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Under normal operation, the daytime running lamps (DRL) module is grounded through circuit 57 (BK).
                Battery voltage is provided to the DRL module through circuit 2002 (OG/BK). When the ignition switch is
                in the ON position, voltage is sent to the DRL module through circuit 489 (PK/BK). The DRL will turn off
                when either of the following occurs:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>When the fog lamps are ON, ground is provided to the DRL module through 1669 (OG/LG).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>When the parking brake is applied, ground is provided to the DRL module through 162 (LG/RD).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>An open in circuit 57 (BK), 489 (PK/BK) or 2002 (OG/BK)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>A short to ground in circuit 162 (LG/RD) or 1669 (OG/LG)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Parking brake switch</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DRL module</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <table id="t1704050" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>PINPOINT TEST A: THE DAYTIME RUNNING LAMPS (DRL) ARE INOPERATIVE</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Step</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A1 CHECK THE DRL MODULE GROUND</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                            DRL Module C1030
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the resistance between ground and DRL module C1030-D, circuit 57
                                            (BK).
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025256.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 5 ohms?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A2.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 57 (BK) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A2 CHECK VOLTAGE TO THE DRL MODULE</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the voltage between ground and DRL module:</para>
                                        <randlist type="dash">
                                            <item>
                                                <para>C1030-G, circuit 489 (PK/BK).</para>
                                            </item>
                                            <item>
                                                <para>C1030-H, circuit 2002 (OG/BK).</para>
                                            </item>
                                        </randlist>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025257.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Are the voltages greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A3.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 489 (PK/BK) or 2002 (OG/BK) for an open. TEST the system for normal
                                    operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A3 CHECK CIRCUIT 1669 (OG/LG) FOR GROUND</emph>
                                </para>
                                <note>
                                    <para>Verify the fog lamp switch is OFF.</para>
                                </note>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the resistance between ground and DRL module C1030-A, circuit 1669
                                            (OG/LG).
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025258.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the resistance greater than 10,000 ohms?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>CARRY OUT the multifunction switch component test. Refer to the Wiring Diagrams
                                    for component testing. If OK, REPAIR circuit 1669 (OG/LG) for a short to ground.
                                    TEST the system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>If the parking brake indicator is illuminated, GO to A4.</para>
                                <para>If the parking brake indicator is not illuminated, INSTALL a new DRL module. TEST
                                    the system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A4 CHECK THE PARKING BRAKE SWITCH SIGNAL CIRCUIT TO THE DRL MODULE
                                        FOR SHORT TO GROUND
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                            Parking Brake Switch C306
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Observe the parking brake warning indicator.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the parking brake warning indicator OFF?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSTALL a new parking brake switch. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 162 (LG/RD) for a short to ground. TEST the system for normal
                                    operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <emph type="italic">Pinpoint Test B: The Daytime Running Lamps Are On With The Parking Brake Set</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Normal Operation</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Under normal operation, the DRL will turn off when the parking brake is applied and ground is provided
                to the DRL module through 162 (LG/RD).
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>An open in circuit 57 (BK) or 162 (LG/RD)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Parking brake switch</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DRL module</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <table id="t1704051" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>PINPOINT TEST B: THE DAYTIME RUNNING LAMPS ARE ON WITH THE PARKING BRAKE SET</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Step</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">B1 CHECK PARKING BRAKE WARNING INDICATOR</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Observe the parking brake warning indicator.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the parking brake warning indicator ON?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to B2.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to B3.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">B2 CHECK CIRCUIT 162 (LG/RD)</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>Parking Brake Switch C306
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>DRL Module C1030
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the resistance between parking brake switch C306-B, circuit 162
                                            (LG/RD) and DRL module C1030-E, circuit 162 (LG/RD).
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025259.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 5 ohms?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSTALL a new DRL module. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 162 (LG/RD) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">B3 CHECK THE PARKING BRAKE SWITCH GROUND</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>Parking Brake Switch C306
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the resistance between ground and parking brake switch C306-A,
                                            circuit 57 (BK).
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025260.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 5 ohms?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to B4.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 57 (BK) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">B4 CHECK THE PARKING BRAKE SWITCH</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Connect a fused jumper wire between ground and parking brake switch
                                            C306-B, circuit 162 (LG/RD).
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025261.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Does the brake warning indicator illuminate?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSTALL a new parking brake switch. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 162 (LG/RD) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <emph type="italic">Pinpoint Test C: The Daytime Running Lamps Are On With The Ignition Switch Off
                </emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Normal Operation</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Under normal operation, when the ignition switch is in the ON position, voltage is sent to the DRL
                module through circuit 489 (PK/BK).
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>A short to voltage in circuit 489 (PK/BK)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DRL module</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <table id="t1704052" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>PINPOINT TEST C: THE DAYTIME RUNNING LAMPS ARE ON WITH THE IGNITION SWITCH OFF</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Step</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">C1 CHECK THE IGNITION SWITCH INPUT TO THE DRL MODULE FOR VOLTAGE
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>DRL Module C1030.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the voltage between ground and DRL module C1030-G, circuit 489
                                            (PK/BK).
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025262.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is any voltage indicated?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>CARRY OUT the ignition relay component test. Refer to the Wiring Diagrams for
                                    component testing. If OK, REPAIR circuit 489 (PK/BK) for a short to voltage. TEST
                                    the system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSTALL a new DRL module. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
